subSubSection.paragraph:
Color
. H. Milne Edwards (
1848
) described the color of this species as “couleur rouge-brun foncée”. Perhaps this description was based on preserved specimen, because Zúñiga-Romero (
2002
) mentioned that (fresh) specimens are white-grayish, with chelipeds yellow. The preserved specimens examined herein present an orangeyellowish color, but in life they present a mixing of white and brown colors, with abundant pilosity.
